OL,3,CMother found dead alongside disabled
OL,4,Cdaughter refused help, inquest hears
OL,6,FNottingham Coroner's Court heard how
OL,7,Fsocial workers, council officers and
OL,8,Fcommunity nursing teams tried to
OL,9,Fengage with Ms Leuga, but that she
OL,10,Fwould often cancel meetings or deny
OL,11,Fthem access to the property.
OL,13,FMs Leuga and her daughter had moved
OL,14,Finto their council home in 2019. Miss
OL,15,FChoulla had Down's syndrome and
OL,16,Flearning difficulties and was
OL,17,F"entirely dependent" on her mother for
OL,18,Ffood and hydration.
